com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message

Class InternalMessage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message.InternalMessage

  • public class InternalMessage
extends Object
    Represents a message instance used by the API for its own internal working. This message will be stored in the InternalMsgQueue
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Neebal Technologies

    • Constructor Detail

      • InternalMessage

        public InternalMessage(Message message,
               int internalMessageType,
               int statusCode)
        Builds an instance of this class and initializes the parameters. By default the instance is created with priority as PRIORITY_NORMAL
        Parameters:
        message - the message originated from the MsgQueue or from the database during the recovery phase
        internalMessageType - the type of this message instance
        statusCode - the status code used to initialize this message instance

      • InternalMessage

        public InternalMessage(Message message)
        Builds an instance of this class on the basis of the Message instance. By default the priority is initialized to PRIORITY_NORMAL. Will be used at the time of getting the message from the message queue by the internal message queue consumer thread.

        Note: Based on whether it is an asynchronous message or no, this InternalMessage instance will mark whether it needs to be persisted in the db or no
        Parameters:
        message - the Message instance to be sent to the server

      • InternalMessage

        public InternalMessage(Message message,
               long timestamp)
        Builds an instance of this class on the basis of the Message and timestamp By default the priority is initialized to PRIORITY_NORMAL
        Parameters:
        message - the Message instance to be sent to the server
        timestamp - the timestamp in millis

      • InternalMessage

        public InternalMessage(int internalMessageType)
        Builds an instance on the basis of the InternalMessageType Initialize the timestamp to the current one and also the priority based on the message type. i.e. Messages other than the type TYPE_LOCAL_CONNECTION_CHANGE will have PRIORITY_NORMAL priority
        Parameters:
        internalMessageType - the internal message type

      • InternalMessage

        public InternalMessage(Message message,
               int internalMessageType)
        Builds an instance on the basis of the internal message type and the Message instance. Initializes the timestamp to the current one and also the priority based on the message type. i.e. Messages other than the type TYPE_LOCAL_CONNECTION_CHANGE will have PRIORITY_NORMAL priority
        Parameters:
        message - the Message instance stored in this InternalMessage instance
        internalMessageType - the internal message type

      • InternalMessage

        public InternalMessage()
        Builds an uninitialized InternalMessage instance
